# Beginner-Friendly Java E‚ÄëCommerce (Spring Boot + Thymeleaf)
# -----------------------------------------------------------
# What you get
# ‚Ä¢ Product listing with image URL, description, price
# ‚Ä¢ Simple shopping cart stored in session (add/remove/update quantity)
# ‚Ä¢ Checkout form (name, email, address) that creates an Order in DB
# ‚Ä¢ Order confirmation page with order id (basic order tracking)
# ‚Ä¢ Sort & filter (by name/price/category + search)
# ‚Ä¢ H2 in-memory database + sample data (no external setup)
# ‚Ä¢ Thymeleaf server-rendered pages (easy to understand for beginners)
# Optional extensions at bottom: reviews, authentication, file uploads, etc.
# -----------------------------------------------------------
# How to run
# 1) Ensure Java 17+ and Maven are installed
# 2) Create a folder (e.g., mini-shop) and place these files with the same paths
# 3) In that folder, run: mvn spring-boot:run
# 4) Open http://localhost:8080
# -----------------------------------------------------------

